quran[399]{c,v,t}:
  51,31,"Abraham said, “Then what is your mission, O messengers?”"
  51,32,"They said, “We have been sent to a wicked people"
  51,33,to send down upon them stones of clay
  51,34,marked by your Lord for the transgressors.”
  51,35,We brought out those believers who were there
  51,36,"but We only found in it one Muslim household [Lot's family]"
  51,37,"And We left there a sign [as a lesson] for those who fear the painful punishment"
  51,38,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Moses when We sent him to Pharaoh with compelling proofs"
  51,39,"But he and his supporters turned away, and he said about [Moses], “A magician or a madman!”"
  51,40,"So We seized him and his soldiers, and cast them into the sea while he was blameworthy"
  51,41,"And [there is a sign in the story of] ‘Ād, when We sent against them the devastating barren wind"
  51,42,It spared nothing it came upon except that it reduced it to ruin and decay
  51,43,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Thamūd, when they were told, “Enjoy yourselves for a while.”"
  51,44,"But they rebelled against the command of their Lord, so the thunderbolt seized them, while they were looking on"
  51,45,"They could not withstand it, nor could they ward it off"
  51,46,"And the people of Noah [were also destroyed] before them. They were indeed a rebellious people"
  51,47,"We built the heaven with might, and We are indeed expanding it"
  51,48,And We spread out the earth. How well did We smooth it out
  51,49,"And We have created everything in pairs, so that you may take heed"
  51,50,"So flee to Allah. Indeed, I am a clear warner to you from Him"
  51,51,"And do not set up another god with Allah. Indeed, I am a clear warner to you from Him.”"
  51,52,"Likewise, no messenger came to those before them without being told: “A magician, or a madman!”"
  51,53,Did they suggest this to one another? Rather they are a transgressing people
  51,54,"So turn away from them [O Prophet], for you are not to blame"
  51,55,"But keep reminding them, for reminder benefits the believers"
  51,56,I have not created the jinn and mankind except to worship Me
  51,57,"I seek no provision from them, nor do I want them to feed Me"
  51,58,"Indeed, it is Allah Who is the All-Provider, Lord of Power, the Mighty"
  51,59,"Indeed, those who do wrong will have a share [of [punishment] like that of their predecessors, so let them not ask Me to hasten it"
  51,60,"So woe to those who disbelieve from [the punishment of] the Day which they are promised"
  52,1,By the mount of Tūr
  52,2,and by the Book inscribed
  52,3,on an unrolled parchment
  52,4,"and by the much-frequented House [in heaven]"
  52,5,and by the canopy raised high
  52,6,and by the sea ever filled
  52,7,The punishment of your Lord will surely come to pass
  52,8,there is none who can avert it
  52,9,On the Day when the heaven will convulse violently
  52,10,and the mountains will move a horrible movement
  52,11,then woe to the deniers on that Day
  52,12,those who amuse themselves in falsehood
  52,13,On the Day when they will be shoved into the Fire forcefully
  52,14,"[They will be told,] “This is the Fire which you used to deny"
  52,15,"Is this [punishment] magic, or do you not see"
  52,16,"Burn in it, whether you bear it patiently or impatiently, it makes no difference to you; you are recompensed only for what you used to do.”"
  52,17,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and bliss"
  52,18,"enjoying what their Lord has given them, and their Lord protected them from the punishment of the Blazing Fire"
  52,19,“Eat and drink pleasantly for what you used to do
  52,20,reclining on lined up couches”. And We will marry them to houris of wide beautiful eyes
  52,21,"As for those who believe and their offspring follow them in faith, We will cause their offspring to join them, and will not detract anything from [the reward of] their deeds. Everyone will be accountable for what he earned"
  52,22,And We will provide them with whatever fruit and meat they desire
  52,23,"They will pass around to one another a glass [of pure wine] which does not lead to idle talk or sin"
  52,24,"They will be served by their servant boys, as if they were well-protected pearls"
  52,25,They will turn to one another with questions
  52,26,"They will say, “Before this, we used to be in awe [of Allah] when we were living among our people"
  52,27,Therefore Allah conferred favor upon us and protected us from the punishment of the Scorching Fire
  52,28,"Indeed, we used to call upon Him before. He is indeed the Most Kind, the Most Merciful.”"
  52,29,"So keep exhorting [O Prophet], for you are not, by the grace of your Lord, a soothsayer or a madman"
  52,30,"Or do they say: “He is a poet for whom we await a misfortune”"
  52,31,"Say, “Wait, I too am waiting with you.”"
  52,32,"Do their minds prompt them to say such things, or are they a transgressing people"
  52,33,"Or do they say, “He has made it [the Qur’an] up”? Rather, they are not willing to believe"
  52,34,"Then let them produce a discourse like this, if they are truthful"
  52,35,"Were they created by none, or were they the creators [of themselves]"
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and earth? Rather, they are not certain in faith"
  52,37,"Or do they possess the treasures of your Lord, or do they have full control [of everything]"
  52,38,"Or do they have a stairway [to the heaven] by which they eavesdrop? Then let those who eavesdrop produce a compelling proof"
  52,39,Or does He have daughters while you have sons
  52,40,"Or are you asking them [O Prophet] for a reward so they find it too burdensome"
  52,41,"Or do they have [knowledge of] the unseen so they are writing it down"
  52,42,"Or do they intend a plot [against the Prophet]? But the plot of the disbelievers will rebound against themselves"
  52,43,Or do they have a god other than Allah? Glory be to Allah far above what they associate with Him
  52,44,"If they were to see pieces of the sky falling down, they would still say, “[This is only] a mass of clouds.”"
  52,45,So leave them alone until they encounter their Day in which they will be struck down
  52,46,"the Day their plots will not avail them in the least, nor will they be helped"
  52,47,"And for the wrongdoers, there will be another punishment before that, but most of them do not know"
  52,48,"Be patient [O Prophet] with your Lord’s decree, for indeed you are under Our [watchful] Eyes. And glorify the praises of your Lord when you rise"
  52,49,And glorify Him at night and when the stars fade away
  53,1,By the star when it sets
  53,2,"Your companion [the Prophet] has neither strayed nor is he deluded"
  53,3,Nor does he speak out of his own desire
  53,4,"It is but a revelation sent down [to him]"
  53,5,"He was taught by [an angel of] mighty power"
  53,6,"and of great perfection, who manifested himself [in his true form]"
  53,7,when he was on the higher horizon
  53,8,"Then he approached [the Prophet] and descended"
  53,9,until he was only two bow-lengths away or even closer
  53,10,Then he revealed to His slave what he had to reveal
  53,11,"The [Prophet’s] heart did not deny what he saw"
  53,12,Do you dispute with him concerning what he saw
  53,13,He certainly saw him a second time
  53,14,"at the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary [in the seventh heaven]"
  53,15,near which is the Garden of Abode
  53,16,"when the Lote Tree was overwhelmed with [divine] splendors"
  53,17,"His gaze did not wander, nor did it look beyond the limit"
  53,18,He certainly saw some of the greatest signs of his Lord
  53,19,"Have you [O disbelievers] thought about [the idols of] al-Lāt and al-‘Uzzā"
  53,20,"and Manāt, the third one as well"
  53,21,Do you choose for yourselves males and for Him females
  53,22,That is then an unfair division
  53,23,"These [idols] are no more than names you and your forefathers have made up, for which Allah has not sent down any authority. They follow nothing but conjecture and what their souls desire, although there has come to them guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,Is it that man can get whatever he wishes for
  53,25,"Rather, to Allah belongs the Hereafter and this world"
  53,26,How many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will be of no avail except after Allah’s permission to whom He wills and pleases
  53,27,"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter give the angels female names"
  53,28,"They have no knowledge about it. They only follow conjecture, but conjecture is of no avail against the truth"
  53,29,So pay no heed to those who turn away from Our message and who only seek the life of this world
  53,30,"That is the limit of their knowledge. Indeed, your Lord knows best who has strayed from His Way, and He knows best who is guided"
  53,31,"To Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is on earth, so that He may recompense the evildoers for what they did, and reward those who do good with the best reward"
  53,32,"those who avoid major sins and shameful acts, except for minor lapses. Indeed, your Lord is ample in forgiveness. He knows you best, as He created you from the earth and when you were fetuses in the wombs of your mothers. So do not claim purity for yourselves, for He knows best who is truly righteous"
  53,33,"Have you seen the one who turned away [from Islam]"
  53,34,"who gave a little, and then stopped"
  53,35,"Does he have knowledge of the unseen, so he has insight"
  53,36,Or has he not been informed of what is in the Scriptures of Moses
  53,37,"and of Abraham, who fulfilled his duty"
  53,38,That no bearer of burden will bear the burden of another
  53,39,and that man will not receive except what he strives for
  53,40,and that his efforts will be examined
  53,41,then he will be recompensed in full
  53,42,and that to your Lord is the final return
  53,43,and that He is the One Who makes people laugh and weep
  53,44,and that He is the One Who causes death and gives life
  53,45,"and that He created the pairs, male and female"
  53,46,from an emitted drop of sperm
  53,47,and it is upon Him to bring about the second creation
  53,48,And He is the One Who enriches and bestows wealth
  53,49,"and that He is the Lord of Sirius [a star worshiped before Islam]"
  53,50,"And that He destroyed the earlier ‘Ād [people of Hūd]"
  53,51,"and Thamūd [people of Sālih], sparing none"
  53,52,"and [He destroyed] the people of Noah before them; they were indeed more wicked and more rebellious"
  53,53,"And He toppled the cities [of Sodom and Gomorrah] upside down"
  53,54,"and they were utterly covered [by stones]"
  53,55,Then which of the favors of your Lord do you doubt
  53,56,"This [Prophet] is a warner like the earlier warners"
  53,57,The imminent Hour has drawn near
  53,58,none but Allah can disclose it
  53,59,Do you find this discourse astonishing
  53,60,"and you laugh [at it] and not weep"
  53,61,while persisting in heedlessness
  53,62,"So prostrate to Allah and worship [Him]"
  54,1,The Hour has drawn near and the moon has split asunder
  54,2,"Whenever they see a sign, they turn away and say, “Same old magic!”"
  54,3,"They deny [the truth] and follow their desires, but every matter will reach its inevitable end"
  54,4,"There have already come to them stories [of destroyed nations] that are sufficient to deter them"
  54,5,"which contain extensive wisdom, but the warnings are of no avail"
  54,6,"So turn away from them [O Prophet]. On the Day when the caller will summon them to a horrific event"
  54,7,"with eyes downcast, they will come out of the graves like scattered locusts"
  54,8,"rushing headlong towards the caller. The disbelievers will say, “This is a hard Day!”"
  54,9,"The people of Noah rejected [the truth] before them; they rejected Our slave and said, “He is a madman,” and he was rebuked"
  54,10,"So he called upon his Lord, “I am overpowered, so help me!”"
  54,11,So We opened the gates of the sky with water pouring down in torrents
  54,12,"and We caused the earth to burst forth with springs, then the waters met for a preordained purpose"
  54,13,"We carried him on an [Ark made] of planks and nails"
  54,14,"sailing under Our [watchful] Eyes; as a reward for the one [they] denied"
  54,15,We have certainly left it as a sign; is there anyone to take heed
  54,16,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,17,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,18,‘Ād disbelieved. Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,19,We sent against them a furious wind on a day of continuous misfortune
  54,20,"sweeping people away, as if they were trunks of uprooted palm trees"
  54,21,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,22,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,23,Thamūd rejected the warnings
  54,24,"They said, “Shall we follow a single human being from among us? Then we would surely be in error and insanity"
  54,25,"Has the revelation been sent down upon him out of all of us? Rather, he is an insolent liar.”"
  54,26,Tomorrow they will know who the insolent liar is
  54,27,"We are sending the she-camel as a test for them, so watch them [O Sālih] and be patient"
  54,28,and tell them that the water is to be shared between them; each should take its drink in turn
  54,29,"But they called their companion, and he undertook the task and hamstrung her"
  54,30,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,31,"We sent against them a single blast, leaving them like trampled hedge-building twigs"
  54,32,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,33,The people of Lot rejected the warnings
  54,34,"We sent against them a storm of pebbles, except the family of Lot whom We saved before dawn"
  54,35,as a blessing from Us. Thus do We reward those who give thanks
  54,36,"He had already warned them of Our punishing assault, but they doubted the warnings"
  54,37,"They even demanded that he let them have their way with his angel-guests, so We blinded their eyes, [saying], “Taste My punishment and My warnings!”"
  54,38,By the early morning a lasting torment overtook them
  54,39,Taste My punishment and My warnings
  54,40,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,41,"Indeed, warnings came to the people of Pharaoh"
  54,42,"But they rejected all of Our signs, so We seized them with the grip of the All-Mighty, Most Powerful"
  54,43,"Are your disbelievers [O Makkans] superior than those, or have you been granted immunity in divine Scriptures"
  54,44,"Or do they say, “We are a united front, bound to prevail.”"
  54,45,"Soon their united front will be defeated, and they will flee"
  54,46,"But the Hour is their appointed time, and the Hour is more catastrophic and more bitter"
  54,47,"Indeed, the wicked are in error and will be in blazes"
  54,48,"On the Day when they will be dragged into the Fire on their faces, [they will be told], “Taste the agony of Hell!”"
  54,49,"Indeed, We have created everything according to a determined measure"
  54,50,"Our command is but a single word, which is fulfilled in the blink of an eye"
  54,51,"We have destroyed many like you [O Makkans]; is there anyone to take heed"
  54,52,Everything they did is in the written records
  54,53,"and everything, small or big, is written down"
  54,54,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and rivers"
  54,55,seated in honor in the presence of the Most Powerful Sovereign
  55,1,The Most Compassionate
  55,2,has taught the Qur’an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,and taught him speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon follow their precise courses
  55,6,"and the stars and trees prostrate [to Allah]"
  55,7,He raised the heaven and enjoined justice
  55,8,so that you may not transgress the limits of justice
  55,9,"Therefore establish weights in justice, and do not give short measure"
  55,10,He has spread out the earth for all creatures
  55,11,in which there are fruits and palm trees with date stalks
  55,12,"and grain having chaff, and fragrant plants"
  55,13,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,14,He created man from dry clay like pottery
  55,15,and He created the jinn from a smokeless flame of fire
  55,16,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,17,"[He is] Lord of the two sunrises and Lord of the two sunsets"
  55,18,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,19,"He merges the two seas [of fresh and salty water] meeting together"
  55,20,yet between them is a barrier so that they do not cross
  55,21,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,22,Out of both of them emerge pearls and coral
  55,23,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,24,To Him belong the sailing ships raised up in the sea like mountains
  55,25,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,26,Everyone on earth will perish
  55,27,"but there will remain the Face of your Lord, full of Majesty and Honor"
  55,28,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,29,All those in the heavens and earth ask of Him; every day He is engaged in some matters
  55,30,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,31,"We will attend to you, O two multitudes [men and jinn]"
  55,32,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,33,"O assembly of jinn and mankind, if you are able to pass beyond the realms of the heavens and earth, then pass; you cannot pass without [Our] authority"
  55,34,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,35,"There will be sent against you flames of fire and smoke, and you will not be able to defend yourselves"
  55,36,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,37,"When the heaven is split asunder and becomes crimson, like red hide"
  55,38,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,39,On that Day no human or jinn will be asked about his sin
  55,40,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,41,"The wicked will be known by their marks, and will be seized by their forelocks and their feet"
  55,42,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,43,"[They will be told] “This is the Hell that the wicked used to deny.”"
  55,44,They will go round between it and scalding water
  55,45,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,46,For those who fear of standing before their Lord will be two Gardens
  55,47,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,48,Shaded by spreading branches
  55,49,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,50,In each there are two flowing springs
  55,51,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,52,In each there are two kinds of every fruit
  55,53,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,54,"They will recline on couches lined with rich brocade, with the fruits of both gardens within reach"
  55,55,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,56,"In them there will be maidens of restrained gaze, untouched before them by any man or jinn"
  55,57,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,58,As if they were rubies and pearls
  55,59,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,60,Is the reward for goodness anything but goodness
  55,61,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,62,And besides these two there will be two other gardens
  55,63,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,64,Both of deepest green
  55,65,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,66,In each there are two gushing springs
  55,67,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,68,"In each there are fruits, palm trees, and pomegranates"
  55,69,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,70,In them there are beautiful noble women
  55,71,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,72,"Maidens with gorgeous eyes, secluded in pavilions"
  55,73,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,74,No human or jinn has ever touched them before
  55,75,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,76,"[They will be] reclining on green cushions and splendid carpets"
  55,77,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,78,"Blessed is the Name of your Lord, the Lord of Majesty and Honor"
  56,1,When the Inevitable Event comes to pass
  56,2,there will be none to deny its occurrence
  56,3,it will bring some low and raise others up
  56,4,When the earth will be shaken violently
  56,5,and the mountains crushed to pieces
  56,6,and turn to scattered dust
  56,7,then you are sorted into three groups
  56,8,the people of the right – how blessed will be the people of the right
  56,9,The people of the left – how miserable will be the people of the left
  56,10,"And the forerunners [in faith] are the forerunners [in Paradise]"
  56,11,"They are the nearest ones [to Allah]"
  56,12,in Gardens of Bliss
  56,13,many from the early generations
  56,14,and a few from the later generations
  56,15,"[They will be seated] on jeweled couches"
  56,16,"reclining on them, facing one another"
  56,17,They will be served by immortal youths
  56,18,"with cups, pitchers, and glasses [of wine] from a flowing spring"
  56,19,which will neither cause any headache nor intoxication
  56,20,along with fruits of their choice
  56,21,and flesh of birds that they may desire
  56,22,"And [they will have] maidens of wide gorgeous eyes"
  56,23,like pristine pearls
  56,24,as a reward for what they used to do
  56,25,They will not hear therein any idle talk or sinful speech
  56,26,"except the words of peace, peace"
  56,27,The people of the right – how blessed will be the people of the right
  56,28,"[They will be] amid thornless lote trees"
  56,29,and clusters of bananas
  56,30,and shade long-extended
  56,31,and flowing water
  56,32,and abundant fruit –
  56,33,neither ceasing nor restricted –
  56,34,"and mattresses raised high [on beds]"
  56,35,"Indeed, We have perfectly created them [their spouses]"
  56,36,and have made them virgins
  56,37,loving and of equal age
  56,38,for the people of the right
  56,39,many from the earlier generations
  56,40,and many from the later generations
  56,41,And the people of the left – how wretched will be the people of the left
  56,42,"[They will be] in scorching wind and scalding water"
  56,43,in the shade of black smoke
  56,44,neither cool nor refreshing
  56,45,"Indeed, they used to be in luxuries before"
  56,46,"and persisted in the gravest sin [of polytheism]"
  56,47,"They used to say, \"When we die and become dust and bones, will we really be raised again"
  56,48,And our forefathers as well?”
  56,49,"Say, [O Prophet], “Indeed, the former and later generations"
  56,50,will be gathered on a predetermined Day
  56,51,"Then you, O misguided deniers"
  56,52,will surely eat from the tree of zaqqūm
  56,53,filling your bellies with it
  56,54,and drinking scalding water on top of it
  56,55,drinking like thirsty camels do.”
  56,56,This will be their welcome on the Day of Judgment
  56,57,"It is We Who created you; will you not then believe [in resurrection]"
  56,58,Have you thought about the semen that you emit
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or is it We Who are the Creators"
  56,60,"We have ordained death among you, and nothing can overcome us"
  56,61,from transforming you and recreating you in forms that you do not know
  56,62,You are well aware of the first creation; why do you not then take heed
  56,63,Have you thought about what you sow
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it grow, or is it We Who make it grow"
  56,65,"If We willed, We could reduce your harvest to crumble, leaving you to wonder and lament"
  56,66,“We suffered loss
  56,67,"rather, we are deprived.”"
  56,68,Have you thought about the water that you drink
  56,69,"Is it you who bring it down from the clouds, or is it We Who bring it down"
  56,70,"If We willed, We could make it salty; will you not then give thanks"
  56,71,Have you thought about the fire that you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who produced its trees, or is it We Who produced it"
  56,73,"We made it a reminder [of the Hellfire] and a benefit for the travelers"
  56,74,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  56,75,I do swear by the positions of the stars –
  56,76,"and this is indeed a great oath, if only you knew –"
  56,77,that this is indeed a noble Qur’an
  56,78,in a well-preserved Record
  56,79,"that none can touch except the purified [angels] –"
  56,80,a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  56,81,Do you take this discourse lightly
  56,82,"and instead [of thanking Allah] for the provision you are given, you show ingratitude"
  56,83,"Then why [you are helpless] when the soul reaches the throat"
  56,84,while you are looking on
  56,85,"when We are closer to him than you, but you do not see"
  56,86,"If you are not subject to retribution, then why do you not"
  56,87,"bring that [soul] back, if you are truthful"
  56,88,If that dying person is one of those who will be brought near to Allah
  56,89,"then [he will have] comfort, fragrance, and Garden of Bliss"
  56,90,If he is one of the people of the right
  56,91,"[He will be told], “Peace be to you, for being one of the people of the right.”"
  56,92,But if he is one of the misguided deniers
  56,93,then he will be welcomed with scalding water
  56,94,and he will burn in Blazing Fire
  56,95,This is indeed the absolute truth
  56,96,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  57,1,"All that is in the heavens and earth glorifies Allah, for He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  57,2,"To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth; He gives life and causes death, and He is Most Capable of all things"
  57,3,"He is the First and the Last, the Manifest and the Hidden, and He is All-Knowing of everything"
  57,4,"It is He Who created the heavens and earth in six days, and then rose over the Throne. He knows all that goes into the earth and all that comes out of it, and all that descends from the heaven and all that ascends to it. He is with you wherever you are, and Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  57,5,"To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth, and to Allah will return all matters"
  57,6,"He causes the night to merge into the day and the day to merge into the night, and He is All-Knowing of what is in the hearts"
  57,7,"Believe in Allah and His Messenger, and spend [in Allah’s cause] out of what He has entrusted you with. For those among you who believe and spend, there will be a great reward"
  57,8,"Why is it that you do not believe in Allah when the Messenger is calling you to believe in your Lord, and He has already taken a covenant from you, if you will ever believe"
  57,9,"It is He Who sends down clear verses to His slave to bring you out of the depths of darkness into the light. Indeed, Allah is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to you"
  57,10,"Why is it that you do not spend in the cause of Allah, when Allah alone will inherit the heavens and earth? Those of you who spent and fought before the conquest [of Mecca and those who did not] are not equal. They are much greater in rank than those who spent and fought afterwards. Yet Allah has promised each a fine reward, and Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  57,11,"Who is there to lend Allah a goodly loan, so He will multiply it for him, and for him there will be a generous reward"
  57,12,"[Remember] the Day when you will see the believing men and women, with their light streaming ahead of them and on their right. [They will be told], “Glad tidings for you Today: gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever.” That is the supreme triumph"
  57,13,"On that Day the hypocrite men and women will say to those who believe, “Wait for us, so that we may have some of your light.” It will be said, “Go back and seek light elsewhere.” Then a wall will be placed between them, which will have a gate, on the inside of which there will be mercy and on the outside there will be punishment"
  57,14,"The hypocrites will call out to the believers, “Were we not with you?” They will say, “Yes, but you allowed yourselves to succumb to temptations, you awaited [some misfortune to befall us], you doubted, and you were deceived by false hopes, until Allah’s decree came to pass. Thus the deceiver [Satan] deceived you concerning Allah"
  57,15,So this Day no ransom will be accepted from you or from the disbelievers. Your abode is the Fire; it is a fitting place for you – what a wretched destination!”
  57,16,"Has the time not yet come for those who believe that their hearts should be humbled at the remembrance of Allah and to the truth that has been revealed? And that they should not be like those who were given the Scripture before, whose hearts grew hard after the passage of long time, and many of them were evildoers"
  57,17,Know that Allah revives the earth after its death. We have made the signs clear to you so that you may understand
  57,18,"Indeed, those men and women who give in charity and lend to Allah a goodly loan, it will be multiplied for them, and for them there will be a generous reward"
  57,19,"Those who believe in Allah and His messengers, it is they who are the people of the truth. And the martyrs will have their reward and their light with their Lord. As for those who disbelieve and reject Our verses, they are the people of the Blazing Fire"
  57,20,"Know that the life of this world is no more than play, amusement, adornment, boasting among yourselves, and a competition in wealth and children. It is like plants that flourish after rain, pleasing the sowers, then they wither and you see them turning yellow, then they crumble. And in the Hereafter there will be severe punishment, or forgiveness from Allah and His pleasure. For the life of this world is no more than a fleeting enjoyment"
  57,21,"Race one another towards forgiveness from your Lord and Paradise the width of which is like the width of the heaven and earth, prepared for those who believe in Allah and His messengers. That is the bounty of Allah which He gives to whom He wills, for Allah is the Lord of great bounty"
  57,22,No calamity befalls the earth or yourselves but it is already written in a Record before We bring it into existence. That is indeed easy for Allah –
  57,23,"so that you may not grieve over what you have missed, nor exult over what He has given you, for Allah does not love anyone who is conceited and boastful –"
  57,24,"those who are stingy and promote stinginess among people. And those who turn away, then Allah is the Self-Sufficient, the Praiseworthy"
  57,25,"We have sent Our messengers with clear proofs, and sent down with them the Scripture and the criteria of justice, so that the people may uphold justice. And We sent down iron, in which there is great might and benefits for people, so that Allah may make known those who help His cause and His messengers without seeing Him. Indeed, Allah is All-Powerful, All-Mighty"
  57,26,"We sent Noah and Abraham, and gave prophethood and Scripture to their offspring: some among them are guided, but most of them are evildoers"
  57,27,"Then We sent Our messengers in their footsteps, and We sent after them Jesus, son of Mary; We gave him the Gospel, and instilled kindness and mercy in the hearts of those who followed him. As for monasticism, they invented it – We did not prescribe it for them – seeking thereby Allah’s pleasure, yet they did not observe it faithfully. So We gave those who believed among them their reward, but most of them are evildoers"
  57,28,"O you who believe, fear Allah and believe in His Messenger; He will give you a double share of His mercy, and will give you a light by which you walk, and forgive you, for Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  57,29,"[This is] so that the People of the Book may know that they have no power over anything of Allah’s bounty, and that all bounty is in the Hands of Allah; He gives it to whom He wills, for Allah is the Lord of great bounty"